If the product passes the inspection it shall be received for return and sent back to the vendor. Delivery costs for the replacement shall be borne by the customer in ‚Äú<em>Customer change of mind</em>‚Äù scenarios. But by Wisaki in case it was a genuine return

A replacement product will also be dispatched to the customer from the merchant‚Äôs inventory.

If a replacement is not possible, Wisaki E-Commerce shall offer the customer a credit note, valid for any other Wisaki E-Commerce purchase and credited to the customer‚Äôs account immediately.

A refund via MPesa / Visa / MasterCard will only be offered in cases where the customer demands one and as a last result. However, priority is given to Wisaki E-Commerce credit notes.

The customer shall be able to track the status of their refund via their account on Wisaki E-Commerce and they shall be notified on email automatically as the status of their refund is updated.[/vc_column_text][woodmart_title align="left" tag="h3" title="Returns Process ‚Äì Vendor Journey" woodmart_css_id="5d481a23c4992" title_width="100"][vc_column_text text_larger="no"]On sign up merchants will be issued with a copy of Wisaki E-Commerce‚Äôs returns policy and return policy exemptions. The merchant will then be asked to agree to or propose changes, based on their products, on the returns policy.

Once they have signed up the merchant and their products will be subject to the standard returns policy and returns exemptions.

The merchant will also advise on their preferred mode of handling returns while signing up. These can include:
<ol>
 	<li>The consignment merchant representative visiting the warehouse to inspect the item and authorize a replacement.</li>
 	<li>The drop shipping merchant having the item sent directly to their business location by Wisaki ECommerce‚Äôs delivery partner.</li>
 	<li>Use Wisaki E-Commerce‚Äôs provided quality check personnel to give a direction on whether to replace item. Final decision to be final to both the customer and the vendor</li>
</ol>
1.4.4 Merchants will be notified via email as soon as a customer‚Äôs request for return of their product is initiated.

1.4.5 The merchant might be called upon to give guidance and or advice regarding a return request on his / her product.

1.4.6 The merchant will be required to collect and replace returned items within 48 hours of their delivery back from the customer.
<ol>
 	<li>In the case of consignment ‚Äì the returned item may be exchanged for one in the warehouse.</li>
 	<li>The consignment merchant will have a choice to replace the returned item immediately or collect it at the end of an agreed period</li>
</ol>
1.4.7 If the merchant is unable to exchange / replace the returned item, they will authorize the issuance for a refund to the customer, to be implemented by Wisaki E-Commerce‚Äôs customer care team.

1.4.8 In a case of a customer refund where the merchant was already paid for the item, the amount shall be deducted from the merchant‚Äôs next settlement.[/vc_column_text][woodmart_title align="left" tag="h3" title="1.5 Refunds" woodmart_css_id="5d481a65184f4" title_width="100"][vc_column_text text_larger="no"]1.5.1 Customer will raise a refund by making a request via chat or writing an email to¬†support@wisaki.com. This is a decision that the business will consider to approve or decline and upon exhausting all other available options

1.5.2 Once a request for return is accepted and an exchange is not possible then a refund will be offered.

1.5.3 All refunds will be carried out within 14 days from the time an authorization is given by the merchant.

1.5.4 Wisaki E-Commerce shall operate on non-cash refund terms mostly, a credit note will be the first and ideal refund mode, however in situations where there is need to refund the customer in cash, authorization/approval shall be sought to refund a customer.

1.5.5 Refunds via cash would be via reversal to the same payment method.

1.5.6 In the following cases store credit might be the only option available for refunds:
<ol>
 	<li>If the amount to be refunded was only part of the order amount and was paid via ¬†¬†debit / credit card</li>
 	<li>If the purchase was done via credit note.</li>
</ol>
